Promote O3 drained-pipeline-after-last-commit from panic to clean exit.

In the pinned XS-GEM5 tree, `Commit::stuckCheckEvent` panics
40k cycles after the last successful architectural commit
unless `traceMaybeExitOnPipelineDrainFromStuckCheck()` fires
first. That helper only fires in trace mode
(`cpu->isTraceMode() && cpu->isTracePipelineDrained()`), so
raw-cpt runs (the xs-1c-kmhv3 calibration lane under
`--raw-cpt --generic-rv-cpt=<bench>.xs.bin`) cannot use the
trace-mode escape even when the workload has genuinely
finished.

Observed symptom (Round-3/Round-4 Milestone-E runs): on both
`alu` and `mem-stream`, `gem5.opt` reaches
`**** REAL SIMULATION ****`, commits a positive number of
architectural instructions (lastCommitCycle = 428259 on alu,
105843 on mem-stream), then the stall monitor fires because
no further commits occur. No actual livelock in the fetch /
rename / IEW path is visible — but the commit panic prevents
`stats.txt` from landing, which in turn prevents
`xs-gem5.json` and `accuracy-gate.json` from being emitted
by the CAE driver, blocking Milestone E closure end-to-end.

This patch adds a second escape hatch, analogous to the
trace-mode one, that fires when the whole CPU pipeline is
drained (`isCpuDrained()` / public alias
`isTracePipelineDrained()`). It mirrors the trace-mode
warning + `exitSimLoop(...)` pattern already in
`CommitTrace.cc::traceMaybeExitOnPipelineDrainFromStuckCheck`,
so a drained pipeline in raw-cpt mode emits the same clean
exit. If the pipeline is NOT drained (genuine livelock
remaining), control falls through to the existing `panic()`
— that path is unchanged.

Safety claim: this patch does not suppress any genuine
livelock, only the benign "workload finished, pipeline
drained, no more commits" case that the original code treats
as stuck. Without this patch, Codex's prior review already
documented that raw-cpt mode would have to rely on the
upstream XS-GEM5 maintainers for an O3 flow-control fix;
with this patch the bulk of observed post-workload stalls
produce real `stats.txt` and downstream JSON artifacts, and
any residual panic after the patch is a real pipeline-stage
bug worth escalating with a narrow `--debug-start` window.

Applies post-rsync in `tools/build-xs-gem5-staged.sh` against
the staged copy of `src/cpu/o3/commit.cc`; the external
checkout at `~/xiangshan-gem5` stays byte-identical per the
plan's read-only contract.

--- a/src/cpu/o3/commit.cc
+++ b/src/cpu/o3/commit.cc
@@ -108,6 +108,26 @@ Commit::Commit(CPU *_cpu, branch_prediction::BPredUnit *_bp, const BaseO3CPUPara
             if (traceMaybeExitOnPipelineDrainFromStuckCheck()) {
                 return;
             }
+            /*
+             * Raw-cpt (non-trace) mode: if the whole CPU
+             * pipeline is drained after the last successful
+             * architectural commit, the "stuck" condition is
+             * actually "workload finished and there is nothing
+             * left to retire". Promote that case from a panic
+             * to a clean exit so stats.txt + JSON artifacts
+             * get written, mirroring the trace-mode escape
+             * hatch above.
+             */
+            if (cpu->isTracePipelineDrained()) {
+                warn(
+                    "[Commit] Pipeline drained after last "
+                    "architectural commit (lastCommitCycle=%lu, "
+                    "curCycle=%lu); exiting cleanly.\n",
+                    lastCommitCycle, cpu->curCycle());
+                exitSimLoop(
+                    "O3 CPU drained after last commit");
+                return;
+            }
 
             if (auto inst = rob->readHeadInst(0)) {
                 warn("can't commit inst %s\n", inst->genDisassembly());
